Enumeration Type Documentation

enum Navico::Protocol::eErrors

Complete set of library specific error return codes.

Certain library methods will be documented to return a sub-set of these errors.

Enumerator
EOK 

The meaning of this and higher levels actually depends on the method called.

ELocked 

Radar has not been successfully unlocked.

EPending 

Operation initiated, completion now pending.

ETimedOut 

Operation timed-out.

EBusy 

Same operation is already in progress and only one can be performed at a time.

EBadSerialNumber 

Invalid serial-number provided.

ENoUnlockKey 

No unlock-key provided.

EBadUnlockKey 

Invalid unlock-key provided.

EWrongUnlockKey 

Wrong unlock-key provided for specified radar.

ENotRunning 

Client has been Stopped.

EUnknownRadar 

Radar has not announced itself to the tMultiRadarClient (requery the radar)

ENonStdAddress 

Radar is not at the standard NRP-1.0 protocol address as required for its unlock level.

ECommsFailure 

Communications failure (problems opening sockets, etc)

EThreadCreation 

Failed to create required threads.

EBadParameter 

One of the parameters is invalid, ie. lies outside its valid range.

EUnused 

End of standardised errors.

EBadUnlockLevel 

The unlock level is too low.
